Attrition Workflow (high level)
library(tidymodels)
library(modeldata)

data(attrition)

attr_split &lt;- initial_split(attrition, strata = Attrition)
attr_train &lt;- training(attr_split)

attr_rec &lt;- recipe(Attrition ~ ., data = attr_train) |&gt;
  step_zv(all_predictors()) |&gt;
  step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors()) |&gt;
  step_normalize(all_numeric_predictors())

attr_spec &lt;- attrition_towers(
  tower_a_units = tune(),
  tower_b_units = tune(),
  fit_epochs    = 20
) |&gt;
  set_engine("keras")

attr_wf &lt;- workflow() |&gt;
  add_recipe(attr_rec) |&gt;
  add_model(attr_spec)

Goal: re-anchor to tidymodels.
Say: - This slide is intentionally “workflow first”. - If people only remember one thing: you still tune with tune_grid().
Classification-specific reminders: - Ensure the outcome is a factor and keep levels stable so dummy columns don’t drift. - Metrics like ROC AUC use class probabilities; confirm the workflow produces them.
